        <abstract> 
<p>DM is highly gratified by CD’s opinion of his labours on boulders [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">12252</hi>]. He owes his start on this subject to CD. Since 1843 he has supported CD’s views on transportation of boulders by ice.</p> 
